<item>
            <title>[LU-9946] Have fileset on default nodemap</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9946</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We would like to be able to impose subdirectory mount for clients in the default nodemap.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Initial implementation done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7846&quot; title=&quot;Impose subdirectory mount via nodemap&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7846&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7846&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was considering default nodemap should not have fileset information, but there are some use cases where it makes sense to define one.&lt;br/&gt;
For instance, it enables restricting mount from clients that do not pertain to any explicitly defined nodemap entry, to a subdirectory with very limited access and content.&lt;br/&gt;
It is also a convenient way to prevent mount from such clients: just define fileset on the default nodemap as a directory that does not exist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will post a patch with my proposal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Sebastien.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
